article.headline: William & Mary 89, Maine 55
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. (AP) -- Corey Cofield had 19 points and nine rebounds as William & Mary beat Maine 89-55 Friday night in the semifinal of the William & Mary Tip-off Classic, the season opener for both teams. William & Mary jumped out to a 7-0 lead in the first three minutes, but 3-pointers from Ernest Turner and Christian Cavanaugh pulled Maine to within one. The Tribe answered with an 11-2 run to go up by 10 with 11:41 left in the half. Maine got as close as six before a 12-2 run put the Tribe up 45-23 at the break. Cofield added seven in the first 5:11 of the second half, followed by a 12-2 William & Mary run fueled by two layups and a dunk from Laimis Kisielius to lead 68-34 with 9:20 remaining. Ernest Turner added 12 in the last eight minutes for Maine, including two 3-pointers and a dunk, but the Black Bears could get no closer than 29 the rest of the game. Turner led Maine with 20, Cavanaugh had 13 and Olli Ahvenniemi added 11. Calvin Baker had 16, including four 3-pointers, for the Tribe. Nathan Mann had 11 points and five steals, and Alex Smith added 10 points. William & Mary held Maine to 36.2 percent shooting, and outrebounded the Black Bears 51-35.
